<TEXT>
Arms plant
rocked by
fresh blasts
BUENOS AIRES: A series of explosions yesterday rocked an arms factory in
central Argentina where a blast earlier this month killed seven people and
injured 330.
Defence Minister Oscar Camilion told reporters the new explosions were caused
by ``spontaneous combustion'', but added that there was no damage to the plant
or its employees.
Police urged residents of Rio Tercero, in Cordoba province, to evacuate the
area. However citizens, remembering the November 3 blast that pelted the area
with shrapnel and bombs, were reportedly evacuating the town.
``We heard an explosion and then saw a smoke mushroom similar to the one we saw
the day of the tragedy,'' said one resident.-Reuter.
</TEXT>
