<HEADLINE>Christmas chart bid by pupils</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<FLAG></FLAG>
<RECORDNO>975208456</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
MORE than 400 Scottish pupils yesterday made a bid for chart success when they
recorded their own Christmas record, with proceeds going to children's
charities.
The children, from Craigie-barns Primary School, Dundee, have recorded two
festive songs, already a hit with parents who have ordered   hundreds of copies
of the              cassette.
Head teacher Ethel Sharp explained: ``We thought it would be a good idea to get
the children more involved in music and raise some money for children's
charities.''
Nursery Rhymes and Santa I'm all Shiver and Shake, were written by Dundee
record producer Bryce Wilder.
</TEXT>
