<HEADLINE>Personal views</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>14</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Correspondence</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>975208517</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
I WOULD like to correct one inaccuracy in your item on our new report, To make
the Parliament of Scotland a Model for Democracy, which makes proposals for how
a future Scottish parliament could work, and in which you describe us as a
``Labour thinktank.''
In fact, the John Wheatley Centre is not aligned to any political party, and
the reports represented the personal views of the two authors, Bernard Crick
and David Millar.
Copies of the report, which argues for cutting out confrontation and ditching
many of the current practices at Westminster, can be obtained from the John
Wheatley Centre, price #5 (including postage).
Richard Norris,
Project Officer,
John Wheatley Centre,
20 Forth Street,
Edinburgh.
</TEXT>
