<HEADLINE>Stuart Henry</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>12</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Obituary</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>975208547</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
FORMER BBC Radio 1 and Radio Luxembourg disc jockey Stuart Henry, who battled
against multiple sclerosis for more than 20 years, died yesterday at the age of
53.
Mr Henry, who was wheelchair-bound, was one of Radio 1's first recruits when it
launched in 1967. He died at his home in Luxembourg where he had lived for the
past two decades. He is survived by his wife, Ollie, a former model. They
married in 1976. The couple had no children.
</TEXT>
