<TEXT>
STEPHEN Gallacher shot a 72, the third lowest round of the day in the European
Tour Qualifying School at windswept San Roque, Spain, yesterday to move within
eight shots of leader Per Nyberg and one behind fellow-Scot Raymond Russell
after the second of the six-round test.
The 21-year-old Bathgate player countered two bogeys with two birdies despite
finding seven bunkers with wayward tee shots over the tight Tony
Jacklin-designed course. Leading scores:
136 - P Nyberg (Sweden) 69, 67. 138 - J Mellor (England) 66, 72. 139 - S
Webster (England) 74, 65; A Lebouc (France) 71, 68; M Wills (Wales) 71, 68; A
Collison (England) 69, 70. 140 - R May (USA) 67, 73; H Buhrmann (S Africa) 67,
73; S Pullan (England) 70, 70; F Larsson (Sweden) 72, 68; R Sailer (Austria)
70, 70.
Scottish scores: 143 - R Russell (Longniddry) 70, 73. 144 - S Gallacher
(Bathgate) 72, 72. 146 - S Henderson (Kings Links) 70, 76. 147 - W Guy
(Buchanan Castle) 73, 74. 150 - A Crerar (Downfield) 71, 79. 155 - B Marchbank
(Marchbank Golf Enterprises) 77, 78. 157 - D Scott (Letham Grange) 81, 76.
q HOLDERS Kilmarnock Barassie remained five adrift after the penultimate round
of the European Club Cup at Vilamoura. Details:
443 - France (Racing Club) 149, 146, 148; Norway (Vestfold Golfklubb) 150,
146, 147. 448 - Scotland (Kilmarnock Barassie) 148, 152, 148 (G Sherry 74, A
