<HEADLINE>Quest can end in victory</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>ROBIN COOK</BYLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>31</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975208581</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
ROUGH Quest can see off the challenge of three previous winners and engrave a
new name on the roll of honour for the Grade 3 Hennessy Gold Cup today at
Newbury.
One Man, Chatam, and Cogent all lock horns in an attempt to become the first
horse since Arkle to lift the brandy twice.
None can be dismissed, with One Man's claims to follow up his victory of last
year particularly strong.
But Rough Quest, whose career really got going at the end of last season,
represents the value to give Terry Casey the biggest success of his training
life so far.
Jenny Pitman's Jibber The Kibber, shock winner of the Tote Silver Trophy at
Chepstow on his reappearance, can once again get the better of Nicky
Henderson's Conquering Leader in the Grade 2 Akzo Nobel Long Distance Hurdle.
</TEXT>
