<HEADLINE>Capper resigns post at James Finlay</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>KRISTY DORSEY</BYLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>21</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975208598</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
WITH Glasgow-based tea trader James Finlay in the final stages of selling its
financial subsidiaries, Richard Capper has stepped down as an executive
director.
Mr Capper served as managing director of James Finlay Bank, the holding company
for the group's financial subsidiaries which are being sold to allow the group
to focus on its core activity of tea trading.
Two financial subsidiaries - Gaelic Invoice Factors and James Finlay Insurance
Brokers - were sold to management buy-out teams for #1.22m.
Finance director Pat Lockett said these disposals would be completed in March,
three months later than planned.
But he added: ``I think everything is in place and we're really sort of down to
the wind-up.''
Those still to go are Warne Investment and Finance Services, James Finlay Bank,
James Finlay Asset Finance, and James Finlay Investment Management.
</TEXT>
