<TEXT>
BBut Beautiful, Brian Lemon (Zephyr)
q Zephyr is a new label owned by one John Bune, a retired businessman who
decided - very wisely - that the best way to invest money he made on the Stock
Market was by recording his favourite jazz pianist - the superb Brian Lemon.
Earlier this year, he gave Lemon carte blanche to make a series of recordings
with his preferred sidemen, and he opted for some of the British jazz scene's
most distinguished players. On these thoughtfully selected 13 tracks, the
ever-classy Lemon is in the suitably distinguished company of guitarist Dave
Cliff, bassist Dave Green, and drummer Allan Ganley.
A Beautiful Friendship, Roy Williams-Brian Lemon Quintet with Warren Vache
(Zephyr)
q Luckily for us, American cornettist Warren Vache (playing at Glasgow's Moir
Hall on Tuesday 28) was in London while the Bune recordings were getting under
way, and he needed little persuasion to guest on this album with old pals
Williams (trombone), Lemon, Cliff, Ganley, and Green. The choice of tunes may
be safe, but the playing - especially Vache's - is hot. Witness in particular
the groovy intro to Comes Love - a foot-stompingly funky cornet fanfare over
jungly-sounding drums - and the fiery duets featuring both Vache and trombonist
Williams on Moten Swing and Just Friends.
</TEXT>
