<TEXT>
JACQUI BURKE - fashion designer
I ACTUALLY bought two brilliant pieces of clothing from this antique and period
costume shop in the Kings Road, London. The first was a padded black biker's
jacket with PVC sleeves - one yellow and the other red. The jacket itself is
really well made with the original mod lining of black and white circles. The
other thing that I bought there and I like to wear with the jacket is an
original black 1950s basque. It's made of real whalebone and is better than
anything that I've ever worn before. It's definitely more comfortable than the
plastic boned basques you get that dig into your skin. This fifties model
actually holds me in and gives me an hourglass figure.
</TEXT>
