<TEXT>
TREVOR SORBIE, the man responsible for creating catwalk hairdo ``The Frizz'', a
pompadour of enraged and artificial static, has supplied us with tips for
looking after tresses this cold season. He says: ``Use a mild shampoo so as not
to strip the hair of essential oils. (That's natural oils, not Neroli or
Eucalyptus.) Massage the scalp to encourage blood circulation and hair growth.
(Your man can do this for you). Gently pat hair to remove moisture, apply
conditioner and comb through hair ensuring that the whole shaft is covered,
from roots to ends.'' (Yawn.)
He continues: ``Blow dry hair using a nozzle and a round, large, bristle
brush.'' (Snore). Hold the dryer, so hot air is blowing down the hair shaft,
and dry hair from roots down. (Big Z's). Pointing nozzle up the hair shaft
forces the cuticles open, leaving hair dull-looking.'' Gosh, is that the time?
</TEXT>
